#Text=Ontario Votes 2007 : Interview with Green Party candidate Torbjorn Zetterlund , Willowdale
#Text=Saturday , October 6 , 2007
#Text=is running for the Green Party of Ontario in the Ontario provincial election , in the Willowdale riding .
#Text=Wikinews ' Nick Moreau interviewed him regarding his values , his experience , and his campaign .
#Text=Stay tuned for further interviews ; every candidate from every party is eligible , and will be contacted .

#Text=Expect interviews from Liberals , Progressive Conservatives , New Democratic Party members , Ontario Greens , as well as members from the Family Coalition , Freedom , Communist , Libertarian , and Confederation of Regions parties , as well as independents .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Why have you chosen to involve yourself in the political process ?
#Text=Why did you choose to run in this constituency ?
#Text=Seven years ago , I had a life-changing experience .
#Text=I was paralyzed from the Guillain Barre Syndrome and spent weeks in hospital unable to move around .
#Text=I 've since recovered but those weeks put things in perspective .
#Text=I had time ; I was removed from my daily life , where like many others I was spending my time chasing a dream of a bigger salary , bigger house .
#Text=I watched TV ; I saw programs about the environment and the effects of global warming and decided I should personally do " something " about it .
#Text=I joined the Green party because the party 's platform reflects my own values with its strong concern for the environment .
#Text=I would like my children and others like them to enjoy clean air , clean land , and clean water and a sustainable future .
#Text=I also believe in serving my community .
#Text=Willowdale is important to me , I have lived in the neighbourhood for seven years , most of the time I 've been in Canada .
#Text=It is place that is welcoming community that represents the best of Toronto .

#Text=I founded [ www . findmore . ca a community neighbourhood website ] , where I write articles on the environment and social issues and engage with members to form neighbourhood groups to discuss how they impact on local concerns .
#Text=I am a volunteer coach for my kids ’ soccer and ice hockey teams because I believe that involving children in a healthy life style is essential to their life-long well-being .
#Text=What prior political experience do you have ?
#Text=What skills and insight can you bring to office , from other non-political positions you may have held ?
#Text=My grandfather was involved in city politics in Sweden and I learnt from , during my military service in Sweden , I was the union leader of the soldiers rights .
#Text=I am a resource manager at a Toronto software firm .
#Text=Coming from the world of project management , I know how to manage , motivate and empower people .
#Text=My business experience has also taught me , that it ’s important to fulfill promises you make to people , a crucial skill for a political representative .
